This JavaScript code for fetching data from an API is giving a `TypeError: Failed to fetch`. What are common causes for this error and how can I fix it?
javascript
async function fetchData() {
  const response = await fetch('/api/data');
  const data = await response.json();
  console.log(data);
}
fetchData();

The following C++ code for a linked list insertion isn't working as expected. It compiles, but crashes when I try to insert a node at the beginning. What's wrong?
cpp
struct Node {
    int data;
    Node* next;
};

void insertAtBeginning(Node* head, int value) {
    Node* newNode = new Node();
    newNode->data = value;
    newNode->next = head;
    head = newNode; // Problem here
}
